# üß† AI Learning Roadmap ‚Äî Strategic Domains for Governance & Compliance

This roadmap outlines key learning areas across foundational and governance-aligned AI domains. Use it to scaffold onboarding kits, stakeholder briefings, or modular training paths.

---

## ü§ñ LLMs, Generative AI & GPT

| **Topic**                     | **What to Learn**                                                                 | **Why It Matters**                                  |
|------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| Large Language Models (LLMs) | Architecture (transformers), training data, tokenisation, fine-tuning             | Understand model capabilities and limitations       |
| Generative AI                | Text/image/code generation, prompt engineering, diffusion models                  | Operationalise creative outputs responsibly         |
| GPT Models                   | GPT-2 to GPT-4/5 evolution, API usage, temperature, context windows               | Build governance-aware use cases                    |
| Prompt Engineering           | Role-based prompting, few-shot learning, system instructions                      | Improve reliability and reduce hallucinations       |
| Evaluation & Metrics         | BLEU, ROUGE, perplexity, human-in-the-loop validation                             | Align outputs with stakeholder expectations         |

---

## üõ°Ô∏è Responsible AI

| **Topic**                     | **What to Learn**                                                                 | **Why It Matters**                                  |
|------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| Fairness & Bias              | Bias detection, mitigation strategies, demographic parity                         | Prevent harm and ensure equitable outcomes          |
| Transparency & Explainability| SHAP, LIME, model cards, documentation standards                                  | Enable auditability and stakeholder trust           |
| Safety & Robustness          | Adversarial testing, fail-safe design, red teaming                                | Reduce risk of misuse or unintended behaviour       |
| Human Oversight              | Escalation protocols, fallback mechanisms, decision support                       | Maintain accountability and ethical boundaries      |
| Lifecycle Governance         | Model registration, versioning, monitoring, retirement                            | Ensure traceability and compliance over time        |

---

## ‚öñÔ∏è Ethical AI

| **Topic**                     | **What to Learn**                                                                 | **Why It Matters**                                  |
|------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| Ethical Frameworks           | UNESCO, OECD, EU AI Act, African Union principles                                 | Align with global and regional norms                |
| Consent & Data Ethics        | Informed consent, data minimisation, purpose limitation                           | Respect user rights and legal boundaries            |
| Algorithmic Accountability   | Decision traceability, audit trails, stakeholder impact assessments               | Support ethical review and boardroom integrity      |
| Cultural Sensitivity         | Ubuntu philosophy, indigenous knowledge systems                                   | Localise AI ethics for African contexts             |
| Dual-Use Risk                | Misuse potential, weaponisation, surveillance                                     | Anticipate and mitigate ethical dilemmas            |

---

## üß≠ AI Governance

| **Topic**                     | **What to Learn**                                                                 | **Why It Matters**                                  |
|------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| Governance Frameworks        | NIST AI RMF, ISO/IEC 42001, OECD AI Principles                                    | Build boardroom-ready governance structures         |
| Risk Management              | Impact assessments, risk registers, mitigation plans                              | Operationalise oversight and compliance             |
| Policy & Regulation          | POPIA, GDPR, EU AI Act, African Union digital charters                            | Ensure legal alignment and cross-border readiness   |
| Stakeholder Engagement       | Communication strategies, transparency reports, public trust                      | Build inclusive and accountable AI ecosystems       |
| Governance Tools             | Model cards, datasheets, AI audit templates, documentation standards              | Enable scalable, repeatable governance practices    |

---

## üèÅ Suggested Learning Path

```markdown
- [x] Completed Intro to LLMs & Generative AI (Microsoft Learn / DeepLearning.AI)
- [ ] Enrolled in Responsible AI Foundations (OpenSAP / World Economic Forum)
- [ ] Drafted Ethical AI Policy for SME Toolkit
- [ ] Mapped AI Governance Framework to POPIA & ISO 42001

üìö Recommended Resources
Microsoft Responsible AI Standard
NIST AI Risk Management Framework
OECD AI Principles
UNESCO AI Ethics Guidelines
ISO/IEC 42001 AI Management System Standard

# üß† Strategic AI Learning Roadmap ‚Äî Skills, Certifications & Badge Tracker

A modular overview of key AI domains for governance professionals, paired with certification pathways and a badge tracker to support scalable, ethical, and compliant AI deployment.

---

## ü§ñ LLMs, Generative AI & GPT

| **Topic**                     | **What to Learn**                                                                 | **Recommended Certifications / Courses**                     |
|------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Large Language Models (LLMs) | Architecture, tokenisation, fine-tuning                                           | DeepLearning.AI LLM Specialisation, Microsoft Learn AI-900   |
| Generative AI                | Text/image/code generation, diffusion models                                      | Google Generative AI Fundamentals, AWS GenAI Essentials      |
| GPT Models                   | GPT evolution, API usage, temperature, context windows                            | OpenAI API Docs, Prompt Engineering for Developers (DeepLearning.AI) |
| Prompt Engineering           | Role-based prompting, few-shot learning                                           | Learn Prompting, Microsoft Copilot Prompting Guide           |
| Evaluation & Metrics         | BLEU, ROUGE, perplexity, human-in-the-loop validation                             | Hugging Face Evaluation Toolkit, Responsible AI Labs         |

---

## üõ°Ô∏è Responsible AI

| **Topic**                     | **What to Learn**                                                                 | **Recommended Certifications / Courses**                     |
|------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Fairness & Bias              | Bias detection, mitigation strategies                                             | World Economic Forum Responsible AI Toolkit, IBM AI Fairness 360 |
| Transparency & Explainability| SHAP, LIME, model cards                                                           | Microsoft Responsible AI Standard, Explainable AI by Google  |
| Safety & Robustness          | Adversarial testing, fail-safe design                                             | NIST AI RMF, Red Teaming for LLMs (Anthropic / OpenAI)       |
| Human Oversight              | Escalation protocols, fallback mechanisms                                         | ISO/IEC 42001, Microsoft AI Governance Framework             |
| Lifecycle Governance         | Model registration, monitoring, retirement                                       | Azure ML Lifecycle Management, AI Audit Templates            |

---

## ‚öñÔ∏è Ethical AI

| **Topic**                     | **What to Learn**                                                                 | **Recommended Certifications / Courses**                     |
|------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Ethical Frameworks           | UNESCO, OECD, EU AI Act, AU principles                                            | UNESCO AI Ethics Guidelines, OECD AI Policy Observatory      |
| Consent & Data Ethics        | Informed consent, data minimisation                                               | POPIA Compliance Training, GDPR for AI Practitioners         |
| Algorithmic Accountability   | Decision traceability, audit trails                                               | AI Ethics & Accountability (MIT / Stanford)                  |
| Cultural Sensitivity         | Ubuntu philosophy, indigenous knowledge systems                                   | African Union Digital Ethics Charter, Localisation Labs      |
| Dual-Use Risk                | Misuse potential, surveillance, weaponisation                                     | AI Risk & Dual-Use Awareness (NIST / NATO)                   |

---

## üß≠ AI Governance

| **Topic**                     | **What to Learn**                                                                 | **Recommended Certifications / Courses**                     |
|------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Governance Frameworks        | NIST AI RMF, ISO/IEC 42001, OECD AI Principles                                    | ISO/IEC 42001 Lead Implementer, NIST AI RMF Practitioner     |
| Risk Management              | Impact assessments, risk registers, mitigation plans                              | AI Risk Management by World Economic Forum, Microsoft AI Risk Templates |
| Policy & Regulation          | POPIA, GDPR, EU AI Act, AU digital charters                                       | AI Law & Policy (Oxford / Stanford), POPIA Governance Toolkit |
| Stakeholder Engagement       | Communication strategies, transparency reports                                    | AI Governance for Boards (MIT Sloan), Ethical AI Communication |
| Governance Tools             | Model cards, datasheets, audit templates                                          | AI Audit Toolkit (AI Verify / Microsoft), Datasheets for Datasets |

---

